THIS IS BULLSHIT!!!

We only had 41 thousand and change at our game on Saturday and we got rediculously loud at several moments in the second half.&nbsp; Pretty close to the noise that I've heard at the Seahawks games I've been to.&nbsp; 

They said it years back when Qwest Field, then called Seahawks Stadium, was in the design stages:&nbsp; Everything about the architecture of the interior that stadium was designed to focus the crowd noise between the hashes.&nbsp; You can stand at the middle of that field and hear someone buying a beer in the back row of the upper deck, but you can't hear the person standing next to you.&nbsp; 

This is just another illustration of the NFL brass getting on their knees for the Manning boys and their teams.&nbsp; Instead of "boo hooing" over this, why don't you go back and try to fix the quality of officiating in the title game?&nbsp; Crossed the goal line my ass.
